<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="P6" checkit-title="Probability with Advanced Counting">
    <statement>
        <p>
            
            
            
                <ol>
                    <li>When drawing a 5 card hand from a standard 52 card poker deck, what is the probability that you draw four Hearts and the Two of Diamonds?</li>
                    <li>From a pool of 40 candidates, 5 people will be selected at random to go on an expedition. They will all be assigned unique tasks. You and 11 of your friends are all in the pool of candidates. What is the probability that a team is selected that  does not include you or any of your friends?</li>
                </ol>
            
            
            
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            
            
            
                <ol>
                    <li>The probability is <m>\frac{(\,_{13}C_4)\cdot 1}{\,_{52}C_5} = \frac{11}{39984}</m></li>
                    <li>The probability is <m>\frac{\,_{28}P_{5}}{\,_{40}P_{5}} = 0.14935988620199148</m></li>
                </ol>
            
            
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
